Key Match Events: Corbin Carroll hit an inside-the-park home run in the first inning
The Dodgers took an 8-6 lead in the ninth inning and held on for the win
Post-Match Reflections: Arizona manager Torey Lovullo said, 'There was a lot of excitement in this building. I felt the energy.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: This was the second time in franchise history the Diamondbacks drew more than 50,000 fans for a regular season game
The game was part of Hispanic Heritage Weekend with a postgame concert from Grupo Control

The Diamondbacks-Dodgers rivalry has heated up in the past year, as Arizona knocked out Los Angeles in the NLDS last October and is fighting to stay within striking distance for the NL West entering September
Others: The attendance on Friday was announced at 46,606
The Diamondbacks play the Dodgers two more times with games Sunday and Monday for Labor Day
